article.headline: Baylor 72, Iona 62
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- LaceDarius Dunn scored seven of his 17 points in overtime as Baylor beat Iona 72-62 on Friday night. Dunn opened the extra session by hitting a 3-pointer and making two of three free throws to put the Bears (4-1) ahead 63-58 with 3:58 left. After Iona (3-2) got within three points, Dunn had a basket off of a rebound to extended the Baylor lead to 67-62 with 1:31 remaining in the Old Spice Classic game. Ekpe Udoh had a basket and Anthony Jones scored on a slam-dunk tip-in to give Baylor a 58-57 lead with 1:34 to go in regulation. Iona tied it at 58 when Scott Machado made one of two free throws 16 seconds later. Iona trailed by nine at the half, 32-23, but went up 52-51 when Jonathan Huffman hit a 3-pointer with 5 minutes to play. Mike McFadden scored 13 points for the Gaels and Huffman added 12.
